ISBh_Vgw/v0/-1x-1.jpg" alt="An oil tanker off the shore of Singapore, on Tuesday, March 17, 2026. A widening conflict in the Middle East has led to dramatic swings and surges in the price of fuel for ships, prompting distributors in Singapore, the world’s top bunkering hub, to cut back their purchases. Photographer: Ore Huiying/Bloomberg" width="580"/&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;div style="display:none"&gt;&lt;![endif]--&gt;&lt;img alt="2026 年 3 月 17 日星期二，新加坡海岸附近的一艘油轮。中东不断扩大的冲突导致船舶燃油价格剧烈波动和飙升，促使全球最大的加油中心新加坡的经销商减少采购。摄影师：矿石慧英/彭博社" src="https://assets.bwbx.io/images/users/iqjWHBFdfxIU/ir51ISBh_Vgw/v0/-1x-1.jpg" style="width: 100%; display: block;" /&gt;&lt;!--[if mso]&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;![endif]--&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p style="line-height: normal; margin: 12px 0 0 0; color: inherit; text-decoration: none; font-size: 14px !important;"&gt;伊朗战争&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2 style="line-height: normal; font-weight: 700; margin: 12px 0 0 0; font-size: 20px !important;"&gt; 12,000 英里的旅程显示全球对柴油的争夺&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p style="line-height: 1.4; margin: 12px 0 0 0; color: inherit; text-decoration: none; font-size: 16px !important;"&gt;飙升的燃油价格迫使石油贸易商进行更长、更陌生的旅程，将货物运送到通常没有什么经济意义的航线上。 &lt;/p&gt;&lt;div style="display: block; width: 100%; height: 40px; text-align: center; line-height: 40px; border: 1px solid; border-radius: 8px; margin: 16px 0 0 0; font-size: 14px !important;"&gt;阅读更多&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="border-top: 1px solid; margin: 24px 0 0 0;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="margin-top: 24px;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://links.message.bloomberg.com/a/sc/1Tf-jSSWSRdk6FhsldHKTgcyYZGLgZ9uluCKe1nnPYKoXTSSj-5sTSLkWvNjQr8tWJGlJRnvNjemo1J6ZFKpPu00WY39izCWh_-oMtAOqieCtS_bduqriPWlZBskO9Xda2wQdIKVfHQj2HVuZ16w1I6sswydRKeKJb5wyokMgsG3TV4U0XHZPWrlJNH51x3smkdWtiw0dZeZ30_fjkg4ER1G0Lvn5Cw9nNwZizCD-4AR6pauUIeUfc1qO0cmiIcOBceCYzB46PWt3Zv7SxPoLxpkd8Pf8CLHH0a_52XYVX9DAzHLPW2_asnGgW3yr54jb-Af4bc2m3EqWPH1lp_o4Y4XYtKehFZFtPx54sAjlahy3Wb2MHekx3GZgHZa81j8Yat5JJxsE-lS361DGkc1/cuP7LWj_lutZ817ZDw2x9IP